---
/**
 * Operator control: the automation boundary (stacked).
 *
 * Verifiable / fast-lane work in the top section; gray-area work in the
 * bottom section, with a deliberate horizontal boundary between them
 * labeled as a product choice. Stacked rather than side-by-side so each
 * section can use the full prose-column width without click-to-zoom.
 *
 * Inline SVG with accessible <title> and <desc>, so text content is
 * indexable by search engines and readable by assistive tech.
 *
 * Used in: content/blog/operator-control-for-agentic-systems.mdx
 */
---

<figure class="diagram diagram--boundary">
  <svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" viewBox="0 0 1320 970" role="img" aria-labelledby="ocBndTitle ocBndDesc" font-family="system-ui, -apple-system, 'Segoe UI', sans-serif" font-size="17">
    <title id="ocBndTitle">The automation boundary in operator control</title>
    <desc id="ocBndDesc">Two sections separated by a deliberate horizontal boundary. The top section shows verifiable work that moves quickly because the feedback loop closes itself: running an approved command, inspecting a file, producing a diff, running tests, fetching an API result, validating structured output. The bottom section shows gray-area work that needs operator visibility because the feedback loop closes through a person: prioritization, customer impact, external messages, public claims, memory boundaries, taste, risk, and deciding when not to proceed. The boundary itself is a violet dashed line labeled as a product choice rather than a default.</desc>
    <defs>
      <marker id="arBnd" viewBox="0 0 10 10" refX="9" refY="5" markerWidth="7" markerHeight="7" orient="auto-start-reverse"><path d="M0,0 L10,5 L0,10 z" fill="#334155"/></marker>
      <style>.lane{fill:#f8fafc;stroke:#e2e8f0;stroke-width:1}.laneLabel{fill:#64748b;font-size:14px;font-weight:600;letter-spacing:.08em;text-transform:uppercase}.cli{fill:#eef2ff;stroke:#4338ca;stroke-width:1.5}.gate{fill:#fee2e2;stroke:#b91c1c;stroke-width:2}.gray{fill:#fef3c7;stroke:#b45309;stroke-width:1.5}.gov{fill:#f5f3ff;stroke:#6d28d9;stroke-width:1.5}.head{font-weight:700;fill:#0f172a;font-size:22px}.lbl{fill:#0f172a;font-weight:700}.sub{fill:#334155;font-size:16px}.note{fill:#475569;font-size:15px;font-style:italic}.dTitle{font-size:34px;font-weight:800;fill:#0f172a}.dSubtitle{font-size:17px;fill:#475569}.colTitle{font-size:24px;font-weight:800;letter-spacing:.04em;text-transform:uppercase}.colTitleAuto{fill:#1e3a8a}.colTitleGray{fill:#7c2d12}.legendText{fill:#334155;font-size:14px}.legendTitle{font-size:13px;font-weight:700;fill:#334155;letter-spacing:.06em;text-transform:uppercase}.boundary{stroke:#7c3aed;stroke-width:2.5;fill:none;stroke-dasharray:8 5}.boundaryLabel{fill:#6d28d9;font-size:15px;font-weight:700;letter-spacing:.05em;text-transform:uppercase}.cardTitle{font-size:17px;font-weight:700;fill:#0f172a}.cardNote{fill:#475569;font-size:14px;font-style:italic}.flag{fill:#15803d;font-size:16px;font-weight:700}.flagWarn{fill:#b45309;font-size:14px;font-weight:700}.flagRisk{fill:#b91c1c;font-size:14px;font-weight:700}</style>
    </defs>

    <!-- Header -->
    <text x="660" y="36" text-anchor="middle" class="dTitle">The Automation Boundary</text>
    <text x="660" y="62" text-anchor="middle" class="dSubtitle">Verifiable work moves fast because the feedback loop closes itself · gray-area work stays visible because the loop closes through an operator</text>

    <!-- TOP SECTION: Verifiable / fast lane -->
    <rect class="lane" x="20" y="86" width="1280" height="380" rx="10"/>
    <text x="44" y="118" class="colTitle colTitleAuto">Verifiable · fast lane</text>
    <text x="44" y="146" class="sub">The system can self-check the work. Run it, watch for errors, move on.</text>

    <!-- 6 boxes in a single row -->
    <g>
      <rect class="cli" x="40" y="180" width="200" height="110" rx="8"/>
      <text x="140" y="208" text-anchor="middle" class="cardTitle">run approved command</text>
      <text x="140" y="232" text-anchor="middle" class="sub">policy-allowed shell,</text>
      <text x="140" y="250" text-anchor="middle" class="sub">scoped tool</text>
      <text x="140" y="276" text-anchor="middle" class="cardNote">exit code is the verdict</text>
      <text x="226" y="200" text-anchor="middle" class="flag">✓</text>

      <rect class="cli" x="252" y="180" width="200" height="110" rx="8"/>
      <text x="352" y="208" text-anchor="middle" class="cardTitle">inspect file</text>
      <text x="352" y="232" text-anchor="middle" class="sub">read · search ·</text>
      <text x="352" y="250" text-anchor="middle" class="sub">diff against base</text>
      <text x="352" y="276" text-anchor="middle" class="cardNote">side-effect-free</text>
      <text x="438" y="200" text-anchor="middle" class="flag">✓</text>

      <rect class="cli" x="464" y="180" width="200" height="110" rx="8"/>
      <text x="564" y="208" text-anchor="middle" class="cardTitle">produce diff</text>
      <text x="564" y="232" text-anchor="middle" class="sub">deterministic,</text>
      <text x="564" y="250" text-anchor="middle" class="sub">reviewable</text>
      <text x="564" y="276" text-anchor="middle" class="cardNote">no commit, no push</text>
      <text x="650" y="200" text-anchor="middle" class="flag">✓</text>

      <rect class="cli" x="676" y="180" width="200" height="110" rx="8"/>
      <text x="776" y="208" text-anchor="middle" class="cardTitle">run tests</text>
      <text x="776" y="232" text-anchor="middle" class="sub">pass / fail is</text>
      <text x="776" y="250" text-anchor="middle" class="sub">the contract</text>
      <text x="776" y="276" text-anchor="middle" class="cardNote">flakes excepted, not normalised</text>
      <text x="862" y="200" text-anchor="middle" class="flag">✓</text>

      <rect class="cli" x="888" y="180" width="200" height="110" rx="8"/>
      <text x="988" y="208" text-anchor="middle" class="cardTitle">fetch API result</text>
      <text x="988" y="232" text-anchor="middle" class="sub">scoped GET,</text>
      <text x="988" y="250" text-anchor="middle" class="sub">schema-validated</text>
      <text x="988" y="276" text-anchor="middle" class="cardNote">read-only, allow-listed</text>
      <text x="1074" y="200" text-anchor="middle" class="flag">✓</text>

      <rect class="cli" x="1100" y="180" width="200" height="110" rx="8"/>
      <text x="1200" y="208" text-anchor="middle" class="cardTitle">validate output</text>
      <text x="1200" y="232" text-anchor="middle" class="sub">schema check,</text>
      <text x="1200" y="250" text-anchor="middle" class="sub">parser contract</text>
      <text x="1200" y="276" text-anchor="middle" class="cardNote">fail loud, never silent</text>
      <text x="1286" y="200" text-anchor="middle" class="flag">✓</text>
    </g>

    <text x="44" y="332" class="head" fill="#1e3a8a">Why this side moves fast</text>
    <text x="44" y="358" class="sub">The feedback loop is closed by the system: an exit code, a schema check, a test result, a parser contract.</text>
    <text x="44" y="382" class="sub">Operator review on this side is sampled and forensic, not sequential.</text>
    <text x="44" y="416" class="note">Slowing this work down with approvals on every step would be miserable.</text>

    <!-- BOUNDARY (horizontal, between sections) -->
    <line class="boundary" x1="40" y1="490" x2="1280" y2="490"/>
    <rect x="500" y="478" width="320" height="26" rx="13" fill="#f5f3ff" stroke="#6d28d9" stroke-width="1.5"/>
    <text x="660" y="496" text-anchor="middle" class="boundaryLabel">The boundary: a product choice</text>

    <!-- BOTTOM SECTION: Gray-area / operator surface -->
    <rect class="lane" x="20" y="520" width="1280" height="430" rx="10"/>
    <text x="44" y="552" class="colTitle colTitleGray">Gray-area · operator surface</text>
    <text x="44" y="580" class="sub">The system can describe the work, but it cannot verify the call. An operator does.</text>

    <!-- 8 boxes, 4 cols x 2 rows -->
    <g>
      <!-- Row 1 -->
      <rect class="gray" x="40" y="608" width="296" height="92" rx="8"/>
      <text x="188" y="636" text-anchor="middle" class="cardTitle">prioritization</text>
      <text x="188" y="660" text-anchor="middle" class="sub">what's worth doing first</text>
      <text x="188" y="684" text-anchor="middle" class="cardNote">no oracle for this</text>

      <rect class="gray" x="352" y="608" width="296" height="92" rx="8"/>
      <text x="500" y="636" text-anchor="middle" class="cardTitle">customer impact</text>
      <text x="500" y="660" text-anchor="middle" class="sub">who feels this change</text>
      <text x="500" y="684" text-anchor="middle" class="cardNote">judgment call</text>

      <rect class="gate" x="664" y="608" width="296" height="92" rx="8"/>
      <text x="812" y="636" text-anchor="middle" class="cardTitle">external messages</text>
      <text x="812" y="660" text-anchor="middle" class="sub">email, Slack, PR comment</text>
      <text x="812" y="684" text-anchor="middle" class="flagRisk">consequential</text>

      <rect class="gate" x="976" y="608" width="296" height="92" rx="8"/>
      <text x="1124" y="636" text-anchor="middle" class="cardTitle">public claims</text>
      <text x="1124" y="660" text-anchor="middle" class="sub">post, ship, publish</text>
      <text x="1124" y="684" text-anchor="middle" class="flagRisk">consequential</text>

      <!-- Row 2 -->
      <rect class="gov" x="40" y="716" width="296" height="92" rx="8"/>
      <text x="188" y="744" text-anchor="middle" class="cardTitle">memory boundaries</text>
      <text x="188" y="768" text-anchor="middle" class="sub">what to remember, scope</text>
      <text x="188" y="792" text-anchor="middle" class="cardNote">scope-defining</text>

      <rect class="gray" x="352" y="716" width="296" height="92" rx="8"/>
      <text x="500" y="744" text-anchor="middle" class="cardTitle">taste</text>
      <text x="500" y="768" text-anchor="middle" class="sub">tone · phrasing · feel</text>
      <text x="500" y="792" text-anchor="middle" class="cardNote">subjective</text>

      <rect class="gate" x="664" y="716" width="296" height="92" rx="8"/>
      <text x="812" y="744" text-anchor="middle" class="cardTitle">risk</text>
      <text x="812" y="768" text-anchor="middle" class="sub">reversibility, blast radius</text>
      <text x="812" y="792" text-anchor="middle" class="flagRisk">always visible</text>

      <rect class="gov" x="976" y="716" width="296" height="92" rx="8"/>
      <text x="1124" y="744" text-anchor="middle" class="cardTitle">deciding when not to proceed</text>
      <text x="1124" y="768" text-anchor="middle" class="sub">stop · narrow · ask</text>
      <text x="1124" y="792" text-anchor="middle" class="cardNote">load-bearing</text>
    </g>

    <text x="44" y="848" class="head" fill="#7c2d12">Why this side stays visible</text>
    <text x="44" y="874" class="sub">No exit code can confirm taste. No schema can confirm "this is the right customer to email."</text>
    <text x="44" y="898" class="sub">The operator owns the call, and the surfaces have to make that call easy. External-action items (red border) carry an explicit guardrail; memory and "when not to proceed" (violet) shape the agent's scope itself.</text>
    <text x="44" y="932" class="note">Slowing this work down with approvals is the point.</text>

  </svg>
  <figcaption>
    Figure 2. The automation boundary is a product choice, not a side effect. <strong>Verifiable work</strong> (top) moves quickly because the feedback loop closes itself with an exit code, a test, or a schema. <strong>Gray-area work</strong> (bottom) stays visible because the feedback loop closes through an operator who weighs taste, risk, customer impact, and the call to stop. The lists aren't exhaustive and the line moves over time, but the shape stays.
  </figcaption>
</figure>
